- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new algorithm for outlier detection in high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in machine learning. 
- cs.DM (Data Mining): Outlier detection is a subfield of data mining, and the paper specifically addresses the challenge of detecting outliers in complex and high-dimensional data. 
- cs.DB (Databases): Outlier detection is also relevant to databases, as it involves identifying unusual or anomalous data points that may affect the quality of the database. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Outlier detection is a common task in artificial intelligence, and the paper proposes a new algorithm that uses a combination of local and global information to improve accuracy. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Outlier detection is also relevant to security and fraud detection, which are important applications of the proposed algorithm.
